7 An Act relating to administration of elections;
amending 26 O.S. 2021, Section 3-130, which relates
8 to post-election audits; clarifying language;
requiring Secretary of the State Election Board to
9 direct all counties to conduct post-election audits
for specified elections; modifying definition;
10 updating statutory language; and providing an
effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 3-130, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 3-130. A. The Secretary of the State Election Board
17 shall have the authority to direct the secretary of a county
18 election board to conduct a post-election audit of election results
19 for any election, for the purpose of maintaining the security of the
20 election system by ensuring that voting devices and software used in
21 a particular election correctly tabulated votes. The Secretary
22 shall direct the secretary of the county election board in each
23 county to conduct a post-election audit following elections held on
24
