1 date s set forth in Sections 1-101, 1-102, 1-103, and 20-101 of this
2 title.
3 B. The method, timing, and procedures for conducting a post-
4 election audit shall be determined by the Secretary of the State
5 Election Board.
6 C. The secretary of a county election board shall report the
7 findings of a post-election audit to the Secretary of the State
8 Election Board, and such report shall be available to the public.
9 D. The Secretary of the State Election Board may promulgate
10 policies, rules, and procedures to implement the requirements of
11 this section.
12 E. For the purposes of this title, a “post-election audit” is
13 defined as means a manual or electronic examination of a limited
14 number of ballots by a secretary of a county election board or other
15 authorized election officials following an election. A post-
16 election audit shall be conducted only at the direction of the
17 Secretary of the State Election Board and only subject to the
18 Secretary’s previously promulgated prescribed policies, rules, or
19 procedures.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
